smith r scott  the wall street transcript r scott smith r scott smith jr is chairman and chief executive officer of fulton financial corporation the largest commercial bank holding company headquartered in the third federal reserve district with  billion in assets and eight banking institutions in pennsylvania new jersey delaware maryland and virginia mr smith joined fulton bank the corporation’s flagship bank as director of personnel in  he went on to assume a variety of positions at the bank before being promoted to chairman president and ceo in  around this time mr smith also assumed additional responsibilities as executive vice president of fulton financial corporation in he was named president and chief operating officer and a director of fulton financial corporation in january  he became chairman chief executive officer and president mr smith is a board member of fulton financial corporation the american bankers association the pennsylvania chamber of business and industry and the economic development company of lancaster county he is also a member of the federal advisory council of the federal reserve the pennsylvania bankers association and the lancaster alliance of which he is a director mr smith earned a bachelor of science degree in finance from the pennsylvania state university he received a master of business administration degree from widener university mr smith is also a graduate of the american bankers association’s national personnel school the stonier graduate school of banking at the state university at rutgers the school of bank management at columbia university and the pennsylvania state university’s executive management program related interviewsfulton financial corporation  r scott smith jroctober   cartlatest newsjames abate of centre asset management sees consumer demand driving new stock highsmalcolm e polley of stewart capital and how to play the health care stockstimothy biltz ceo of lumos networks identifies the key component for future 